❯ podman artifact inspect quay.io/crio/artifact@sha256:d2dbbc46e94529be98d2513fe2a46ef650683af96c584e1287dd966300aaf583
Error: quay.io/crio/artifact@sha256:d2dbbc46e94529be98d2513fe2a46ef650683af96c584e1287dd966300aaf583: artifact does not exist
```

Also latest tag is not automatically appended to the artifact name.
```
❯ podman artifact inspect quay.io/crio/busybox
Error: quay.io/crio/busybox: artifact does not exist

❯ podman artifact inspect quay.io/crio/busybox:latest
{
     "Manifest": {
          "schemaVersion": 2,
          "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json",
          "config": {
               "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.config.v1+json",
               "digest": "sha256:eb13477d9ef899224bc2dea9698a335e9cf9df1a8d284a26a0c8797444a74202",
               "size": 594
          },
          "layers": [
               {
                    "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.layer.v1.tar+gzip",
                    "digest": "sha256:f70adabe43c0cccffbae8785406d490e26855b8748fc982d14bc2b20c778b929",
                    "size": 723172
               }
          ]
     },
     "Name": "quay.io/crio/busybox:latest",
     "Digest": "sha256:f2463a82068a315d4661261907dcc33b6daac88ec2082eddb755bd061660f9ae"
}
```

Those behaviors are also different from images. Are they also intentional?
If I should open a new issue for it, feel free to close this issue and I'll open a new one.

Correct, shortnames should not be used.  We can enforce that reasonably simply. 

 After talking with @mtrmac , I will make a proposal for a new type of `ArtifactReference` which would contain something like a `namedD`.  Then we'd have a New constructor that would do all the validation of "rules" and return an error on the invalid reference.  This would become a type change, however, so would everyone be cool with that ?

